              </gmd:dateType>
            </gmd:CI_Date>
          </gmd:date>
        </gmd:CI_Citation>
      </gmd:citation>

      <gmd:abstract>
        <gco:CharacterString>
          The Eocene Marine Ostracod Database (EMO) compiles taxonomy, occurrence records, 
          and reference information for marine ostracods from the Eocene epoch. 
          The dataset is distributed as curated CSV files (taxonomy_info, occurrence_record, 
          reference_list) under the MIT License and maintained in a version-controlled 
          GitHub repository. The database is designed to support reproducible paleobiological 
          and stratigraphic research and includes explicit documentation of spatial 
          uncertainty and data lineage.
        </gco:CharacterString>
      </gmd:abstract>

      <gmd:purpose>
        <gco:CharacterString>
          To provide an open-access, reproducible database for Eocene marine ostracod 
          taxonomy and occurrences, enabling transparent scientific reuse and long-term 
          data preservation.
        </gco:CharacterString>
      </gmd:purpose>

